window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>A new thriller based on the true story of LA’s first known serial killer.</b></p> <p>In 1919, Kathryn Wombacher finds a lonely-hearts ad placed by one Walter Andrew:</p> <p><i>\"Would be pleased to correspond with a refined young lady or widow. Object, matrimony.”</i></p> <p>Kathryn and Walter fall in love and marry within weeks.</p> <p>What Kathryn doesn’t know...is that her new husband is really James “Bluebeard” Watson, a notorious West Coast serial killer who catfished and married 22 women, murdering 10.</p> <p>Based on newly unearthed evidence, <i>Bluebeard </i>is the definitive story of a sociopath who wielded love as a deadly weapon.</p> <p>And it’s the story of a woman who discovered the unthinkable about her husband...and dared to fight back.</p>"; 
